The Public Health Laboratory Service national case-control study of primary indigenous sporadic cases of campylobacter infection. The aetiology of sporadic campylobacter infection was investigated by means of a multicentre case-control study. During the course of the study 598 cases and their controls were interviewed. Conditional logistic regressional analysis of the data collected showed that occupational exposure to raw meat (odds ratio [OR] 9.37 95% confidence intervals [CI] 2.03, 43.3), having a household with a pet with diarrhoea (OR 2.39